call the game in
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to cease doing something; to admit that one has had enough (phr. from cards or sport on analogy of analogy of `call something off' and `throw one's hand, the sponge in'; or `call in one's bets, or credit or `a mortgage' =`foreclose' etc).
